\noindent second solution to (18.147) as a linear combination of (18.148) and (18.149) given by
\begin{align*}
   \begin{split}
    \textit{U(a,c;x)}\equiv \frac{\pi}{sin \pi c} \bigg[\frac{M(a,c;x)}{\Gamma(a-c+1)\Gamma(c)}-x^{1-c}  \frac{M(a-c+1,2-c;x)}{\Gamma(a)\Gamma(2-c)} \bigg].
    \end{split}
\end{align*}
\noindent This has a wll behaved limit asa c approaches an integer
